The paper deals with extending the language of disjunctive hybrid probability logic programs (DHPP) to allow arbitrary probability aggregates, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the semantics of DHPP with probability aggregates, which involves concepts from programming languages and formal methods (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the importance of nonmonotonic probability reasoning, which is relevant to computational engineering (cs.CE).
